\section{EXPERIENCE}
\par
\textbf{Hilbert Meets Isabelle}\\ 
Formalizing Matiyasevich's proof of Hilbert's 10th problem on Isabelle/HOL, supervised by Prof. Dierk Schleicher and Prof. Yuri Matiyasevich, 2017-2018. Publication: \url{https://easychair.org/publications/preprint/GhvC}
\par
\textbf{Teaching Assistant (TA)}\\
September 2018 - December 2019\\
TA for Analysis I in Fall 2018, Analysis II in Spring 2019 and Calculus on Manifolds in Fall 2019.\\
Task was to grade weekely homeworks, hold tutorials and/or office hours.

\section{ACTIVITIES}
\par
\textbf{Differential Geometry Summer School:} Participated in Differential Geometry Summer School organized by University of Lisbon in July 2018. The details can be found on  \url{https://www.math.tecnico.ulisboa.pt/~ggranja/Talentos/school2018/program.html}
\par
\textbf{Guided Study of Mathematical Physics}
Studied functional analysis, quantum mechanics and mean field theory during summer 2018 under guidance of Prof. S\"oren Petrat. Studied the papers ``A Simple Derivation of Mean Field Limits for quantum systems'' by Peter Pickl and ``Instabilities in the Mean Field Limits'' by Daniel Han-Kwan and Toan Nguyen.
\par
\textbf{Algebraic Geometry Learning Seminar:} Organized a student seminar on basic algebraic geometry in Fall 2018. Interested students met once a week, alternating between talk session and problem solving session. Covered commutative algebra, affine and projective varieties, sheaves and Cech cohomology.
\par
\textbf{Park City Mathematics Institute:} Participated in the Park City Mathematics Institute 2019 (July 1 to July 20). The main topic of the program was ``Quantum Field Theory and Manifold Invariants''. For undergraduates, there were two lecture series: one on ``Gauge Theory, Gravitation and Geometry'' and the other on ``Low Dimensional Topology''.
\par
\textbf{Lie Groups and Lie Algebras Learning Seminar:} Organized a student seminar on Lie Groups, Lie Algebras and their Representations in Fall 2019. Covered classification of abelian lie groups, basic Representation Theory, representation of $\mathfrak{sl}_2(\mathbb{C})$, Young Diagrams, semisimple, solvable and nilpotent lie algebras, Root systems, Dynkin diagrams.
\par
\textbf{Member of Jacobs University Math Society:} Been a member of Jacobs University Math Society since September 2017. Attended regular meetings and also gave couple of talks.
\par
\textbf{International Physics Olympiad:} One of the five participants from Nepal on International Physics Olympiad 2015 (in India) and 2016 (in Switzerland and Lichtenstein).

